---
import Base from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailCTA from '../../components/EmailCTA.astro';
import { applications } from '../../data/applications';
const schema={'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'CollectionPage',name:'Oil-Immersed Transformer Temperature Monitoring Solutions',description:'Engineering application guidance for transformer oil and winding temperature monitoring, cooling control, remote signals and retrofit projects.'};
---
<Base title="Transformer Temperature Monitoring Solutions | INNO" description="Plan oil-immersed transformer temperature monitoring for power and distribution units, cooling control, remote signals and controller retrofit projects." schema={schema}>
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Oil-immersed transformer applications</p><h1>Transformer Temperature Monitoring Solutions</h1><p>Define the thermal variable, operating decision, signal path and installation interface before selecting an OTI, WTI, BWY, BWR or digital monitoring device.</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="answer-block"><strong>Application planning answer.</strong> A transformer temperature monitoring solution coordinates the field measurement, local indication, cooling contacts, alarm or trip outputs and remote data path. Product selection follows the transformer design and operating purpose.</div><div class="section-head"><h2>Choose a Transformer Temperature Monitoring Application</h2></div><div class="grid two">{applications.map(item=><article class="card"><h3><a href={`/applications/${item.slug}/`}>{item.title}</a></h3><p>{item.intro}</p><a class="arrow" href={`/applications/${item.slug}/`}>Plan {item.title.toLowerCase()}</a></article>)}</div></div></section>
  <section class="section tint"><article class="container prose"><h2>What must be defined before selecting the monitoring system?</h2><p>State whether the project needs transformer top-oil temperature, traditionally simulated winding temperature or another direct measurement. Then define the local display, cooling stages, alarm and trip philosophy, remote interface, receiving equipment and commissioning method.</p><h3>Connect OTI and WTI values to the correct operating decision</h3><p>An OTI follows top-oil temperature at a specified thermometer pocket. A WTI adds a load-current-related thermal simulation. Their contacts and remote tags should retain those identities so operators do not treat unlike values as the same temperature.</p><h3>Use application pages to select a product path</h3><p>After reviewing the application, compare <a href="/products/transformer-oil-temperature-indicators/">transformer oil temperature indicators</a>, <a href="/products/transformer-winding-temperature-indicators/">transformer winding temperature indicators</a> and <a href="/products/transformer-temperature-monitoring-devices/">remote monitoring devices</a>.</p></article></section>
  <EmailCTA title="Plan a Transformer Temperature Monitoring Solution" subject="Transformer temperature monitoring application review" />
</Base>
